The South African opposition party will table a private members bill to change the Public Finance Act and the Municipal Finance Management Act to ensure national and provincial governments procure 80% of their goods and products from local producers of which 50% must be women and the youth. All Commissions were filled with delegates that made valuable contributions. #EFFNPA2019 pic.twitter.com/D1vfLZSpYd Senior EFF member in Limpopo, George Raphela, says they will also help finalise legislation that penalises companies who evade tax. “The second National Prosecution Authority resolve to finalise the general Anti-Avoidance Tax Bill which seeks to criminalise all forms of tax avoidance and illicit financial flows. Multinational companies who operate in South Africa and who engage in tax avoidance and illicit financial flows will have their assets nationalised.”
